div1.p: United States of America, ss:
The President of the United States of America,
To the Honorable the Judges of the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington, Greeting:

Whereas, lately in the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington, before you, or some of you, in a cause between entitled In the matter of the application of Chin Quock Wah for a writ of habeas corpus, No. 2971, wherein the final order of the said District Court, entered in said cause on the 29th day of May, A. D. 1915, was against the said Chin Quock Wah.

as by the inspection of the transcript of the record of the said District Court, which was brought into the Supreme Court of the United States by virtue of an appeal taken by the said Chin Quock Wah, whereon Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration at Seattle, Washington, was made the party appellee, agreeably to the act of Congress, in such case made and provided, fully and at large appears.

And whereas, in the present term of October, in the year of our Lord one thousand nine hundred and fifteen, the said cause came on to be heard before the said Supreme Court, and it appearing to the Court that the parties have failed to print the transcript of the record,

It is, therefore, in pursuance of the tenth rule of this Court, now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this Court that th is appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed with costs; and that the said Henry M. White, Commissioner etc., recover against the said Chin Quock Wah for his costs herein expended and have execution therefor.
April 3, 1916.

You, therefore, are hereby commanded that such execution and proceedings be had in said cause, as according to right and justice, and the laws of the United States, ought to be had, the said appeal notwithstanding.
Witness the Honorable Melville W. Fuller, Edward D. White, Chief Justice of the United States, the eighteenth day of May, in the year of our Lord one thousand nine hundred and sixteen.
Costs of Henry M. White, Commissioner etc.
